Paper: hep-th/9908126

Date: 1999-08-19

Title: Non-BPS Dirichlet branes

Authors: Oren Bergman and Matthias R Gaberdiel

Comments: 10 pages, LATEX; submitted to Proceedings of Strings '99

Journal-ref: Class.Quant.Grav. 17 (2000) 961-969

A brief introduction to the boundary state approach to Dirichlet branes isgiven. The example of the non-BPS D-string of Type IIA on K3 is analysed insome detail, and its dual heterotic state is identified.